{
  "stem": "13817.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "One-- then after awhile one of the big Nazis who took the same train every morning that I took, came over and told the boys they couldn't sit there with me playing cards anymore.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I had to sit in the last wagon of the train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the boys moved-- some of them moved with me there to show support, but he harassed them so much that they later on gave up on it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "In fact, one of the boy who still tried to stay with me all of a sudden he got this notice to go into the army.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He was drafted because-- I'm quite sure because of that, that he didn't follow the Nazi line there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then also and I remember being on the train and always being in the last wagon, being harassed on-- by this Nazi.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then one day, all of a sudden, they burned all the books, I think was also '33 or '34.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "All the books of the Jewish artists, all the books what didn't compile with the Nazi ideas.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The books of all these-- these big Jewish authors like Heine, Mann, Einstein.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Then the books written by socialists.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "In fact, the-- the US Constitution were burned because the big universities-- the university made a big show of it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "The fraternities there, each had a special different uniform.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "The Germans were big on uniforms, so they made a big parade out of them, a big bonfire, and burned all them books.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And now they were-- would be happy to have them back because it is manuscripts in there, but never can be replaced.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "This was things what was going on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Then in 1935, these so-called Nuremberg Laws.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "You couldn't marry non-Jews anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "You had to-- the race laws, the so-called race laws.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
